					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Skidlz wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Strange that writing there (in cpu) during vblank offsets sprites.</div>
<br />That probably happens due to mirroring. The wiki says that <a href="http://nesdevwiki.org/wiki/index.php/NES_CPU#CPU_Memory_Map" class="postlink">$23C0 is in a erea that mirrors the PPU registers</a>, so when you wrote stuff there you were actually affecting <a href="http://nesdevwiki.org/wiki/index.php/NES_PPU#PPUCTRL_.28.242000.29" class="postlink">register $2000</a>, which controls a few parameters of sprites and background.</div>

